h1.a: WLISD to Remain Closed Through End of 2019-2020 School Year

section.p:
Today, April 17th, Governor Greg Abbott ordered all schools to remain closed for the rest of the school year. This is a harsh reality, and a genuine loss – for teachers who miss their students, students who miss their teachers, and especially for our graduating seniors.
Wink-Loving ISD will continue providing instructional materials and feedback to our students throughout the remainder of the year. We will be working in the upcoming days to develop a plan for rest of the year and end of the year activities for our students.
To our Seniors - Mrs. Gibson will be reaching out to you sometime next week (probably midweek) to schedule a time to meet with you about year-end activities.
Together, we will get through the current challenge as we continue to focus on what's important – the safety and well-being of our students and staff. Please continue to pray for health and healing for our community. #WildcatPride

section.p: Wink Elementary is currently re-working our instructional packet pick-up/ drop-off process. Please have your son/daughter continue to work on their current assignments. More information will be available soon. The pick-up/drop-off for next Tuesday (April 14th) is currently cancelled.

h1.a: WLISD COVID-19 Grading Policy - 6th Six Weeks

section.p:
Registration packets for the 2020-2021 school year have been mailed to all incoming 7th-12th graders. These packets are due back to Mrs. McGehee in the office no later than May 4th.
Please be on the lookout for these packets...it's extremely important that they are returned completely filled in.

h1.a: National Honor Society Coin Drive Raises $739

section.p: A total amount of $739.00 was collected in the coin drive sponsored by the National Honor Society. This amount will be donated to the Crisis Center in Odessa in the form of a monetary donation or supplies they need to keep in the center for women and children they service.
